parameters: 3.イベント後のプレイヤーの位置
One-armed Opro: W-What is that...? Is it a demon...?
Swift Celis: 'Clea! I'm going to provide support!'
Clea: Their companions are being attacked.

Clea: So please, leave it to us! If we lose, we'll leave it
to Celis-san and Opro-san.
Clea: Please face this way! Your opponent is here!

Mage Relm: Please don't say such unlucky things. Well,
there's no way we would lose!

Priestess Sophia: Oh my, are you saying that we won't lose
so easily?

Thief Nora: If you're the one who scared that child, I
won't forgive you!
Clea: Now, it's time to battle.

Mage Relm: Are you still moving?! You have no sense of
surrender, huh? In that case, I'll use my magic to--

Swift Celis: Hehe, you didn't let your guard down until the
end, huh?
Clea: Yes, thank you very much.

One-armed Opro: This child is also safe. Let's return to
our comrades.

One-armed Opro: Well then, shall I conduct a little
investigation?

Clea: Were they your family? Either way, I'm glad we were
able to reunite.

Mage Relm: What could this be? It looks like a pedestal for
a ritual or perhaps an altar.

Priestess Sophia: I wonder if this place has nothing to do
with Pluus?

Thief Nora: I feel like those children were desperately
protecting this place. Even if it has nothing to do with
Pluus, it's still a meaningful location!

One-armed Opro: I agree, there is something here. This
place feels like a different world, with a different sense
of common sense than the Imperial mainland.

Swift Celis: Pluus...! Could it be that Pluus refers to
this?

Swift Celis: That is the grave of Pluus, and these children
were protecting it.
Mage Relm: That hypothesis is too convenient for us--

Mage Relm: W-What is this...!? Debris regenerating within
the light, time rewinding...

One-armed Opro: May I read it? Miss Mage, sorry to bother
you, but I'll need your assistance.

One-armed Opro: I apologize to my fellow Ftera comrades who
fought together for freedom, but as adventurers, we have to
accept that this is how it is and we were sent off with
disappointment.

One-armed Opro: Escorted by a strange bard, I embarked on
an adventure that has been my lifelong dream of discovering
a new continent.

One-armed Opro: As I thought, it was true that there would
be something beyond the demon-infested waters.

One-armed Opro: I investigated the interior of the ruins
with excitement, as it had a shape I had never seen before,
but a problem arose...

Mage Relm: Um, because the monster that was supposed to
eliminate the intruders started moving, it ended up exposing
[them] to danger.

Mage Relm: And in the midst of the battle with a large
number of monsters, I ended up sustaining a serious injury.

One-armed Opro: When I woke up, there was a large creature
with dog-like ears tending to my injuries.

One-armed Opro: I had a terminal illness and realized my
time was running out, so that's why I embarked on this final
adventure.

One-armed Opro: The only thing I could do in my situation
was to hand over the ship to the person who saved my life,
who seemed to be a fellow castaway.

One-armed Opro: At the end of my happy life, I was able to
make a new friend...

One-armed Opro: Above all else, everything I have aimed for
is beyond this point.
Swift Celis: Will you take me beyond this wall?

Swift Celis: Let's go see everything that Poosu aimed
for...
3.イベント後のプレイヤーの位置
3.イベント後のプレイヤーの位置
Cleric Sophia: Hic... Relm-chan, let's give up already.

Mage Relm: I will never give up! I can't stand the thought
of ancient texts that I can't decipher!

Cleric Sophia: Is it a time delay? It seems like the
characters are appearing on the stone tablet.

Mage Relm: Ah! These characters are different from any that
I know!

Mage Relm: If there's someone who can read this, they must
be a super genius!
Thief Nora: Can you show it to me?
Mage Relm: I think it's a futile effort, but go ahead!

Clea: Mr. Opro, is it safe to say that this completes the
request?

One-armed Opro: Ah, thank you so much. I have finally been
able to fulfill the promise with my long-time friend.

One-armed Opro: With this, there is nothing left to
regret--

Mage Relm: C-Can you really read it!? You're not just
saying random things, right? Can I trust you!?

Thief Nora: My friend, our benefactor... Let us praise him,
the great warrior, who is of the same race as us.

Thief Nora: I think I came from the continent I saw
earlier, probably. I was on a ship and got carried away to
the Empire...

Thief Nora: That's my hometown... Guh, I can't even
remember the words, but that's my hometown.

Thief Nora: I came from there and was able to meet
everyone... *sniff*

One-armed Opro: If that's correct, then the continent I saw
is Paraxeno, where the beastmen live.

One-armed Opro: Beyond that, there should be a crypt called
the Phantom Continent.

One-armed Opro: Hahaha, the dream isn't over yet. The world
is still filled with wonders.

One-armed Opro: Let's continue the conversation we had
earlier at the entrance.

One-armed Opro: Right now, it would be better to stay by
your friend's side.
One-armed Opro: May I hold onto this Pruce's diary?

Swift Celis: I want to take him on an adventure again, if
possible, with this sword.
Swift Celis: Hehe, I wonder if everything will be alright?
Clea: Let's go soon. Another monster might appear.
Swift Celis: Maybe the time has come.

Swift Celis: Even though it was only for a short while, I'm
glad I could go on an adventure with Clea.

Clea: Yes, let's continue taking on requests together from
now on.
3.イベント後のプレイヤーの位置
